Project: INNOPLE Loyalty Platform
Type: Multi-tenant SaaS loyaltysystemAll entities must include tenantIdfor multi-tenancy.

Pointsystem must follow Ledger-based design:- Use PointLotfor earned points- Use PointLedgerfor event history- Use PointAllocationfor lot deduction tracking- Use PointAccount.currentBalanceas cached balance

Deduction logic must follow FEFO:-Orderby expiresAtASC, createdAtASCAll point operations (earn, use, manualExpire, autoExpire)
must be handled inside a single transactional service.

Never directly modify currentBalancewithout creating Ledgerand Allocation records.

Use optimistic lockingfor PointAccount.

Code must be scalableand enterprise-ready.
Avoidover-simplified CRUD-only design.

All repository queries must filter by tenantId.
Never allow cross-tenant data access.

If tenantId is missing, reject the request.

Tenant context must be resolved from request header or authentication context.
Do not trust client-provided tenantId blindly.
